        <item>
        <title>Hugo&#43;Github</title>
        <link>https://yanzhang-xu.github.io/p/hugo-github/</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 07 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://yanzhang-xu.github.io/p/hugo-github/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="https://yanzhang-xu.github.io/p/hugo-github/cat.png" alt="Featured image of post Hugo&#43;Github" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;This article offers steps to build a blog.(Assume the hugo has been installed properly in your PC.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.jianshu.com/p/e399a96bba2d&#34; style=&#34;display:inline;color:#516b91;&#34;&gt;Hugo install&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;bp-styledisplayinlinecolor516b91a-hrefhttpsthemesgohugoiothemes-clone-the-theme-from-the-github-repositoryapb&#34;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;p style=&#34;display:inline;color:#516b91&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://themes.gohugo.io/themes/&#34;&gt; Clone the theme from the github repository&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;pre&gt;
    hugo new site your-site-name   ## build your site
    cd your-site-name/themes      ## change the direction to your-site-name/themes
    git clone https://github.com/author/theme-name.git  ## replace the &#34;author&#34; and &#34;theme-name&#34;
    cd ..                         ## change the direction to your-site-name
    cp -r /themes/theme-name/exampleSite/*   
    ## copy the files in /themes/theme-name/exampleSite/ to your site folder(your-site-name)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note** There are two config files ( &lt;b&gt;config.toml&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;hugo.yaml&lt;/b&gt; ) in your site floder. You need to copy the items in &lt;b&gt;hugo.yaml&lt;/b&gt; to &lt;b&gt;config.toml &lt;/b&gt;, and delete the &lt;b&gt;hugo.yaml&lt;/b&gt;. You can change the type of config file, either &lt;b&gt;config.toml &lt;/b&gt; or &lt;b&gt;config.yaml &lt;/b&gt; is ok. I prefer&lt;b&gt;config.yaml &lt;/b&gt;.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;example1.png&#34; alt=&#34;stpe2&#34;&gt;
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;bbuild-the-blog-b&#34;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Build the blog &lt;/b&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;pre&gt;
hugo server -D   
## in your-site-name folder, run the code, you can see the website in local
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are some errors like.&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
1.empty website: ensure the exampleSite has been copyed to your-site-name folder and config.toml has been modified.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&#34;display:inline;color:#516b91&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/CaiJimmy/hugo-theme-stack/issues/976&#34;&gt;2. &#34;render of &#34;taxonomy&#34; failed: execute of template failed&#34; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; : upgrade the version of Hugo.
For windows: your can download the latest version of Hugo, and replace the previos &lt;b&gt;.exe &lt;/b&gt; file.
&lt;h3 id=&#34;bpush-the-public-folder-to-your-github-repositoryb&#34;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Push the Public folder to your Github repository&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;For more information to build the your repository in the github, you may refer to the &lt;a href=&#34;https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/58254227&#34; style=&#34;display:inline;color:#516b91;&#34;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
cd pubilc    ## run the previous code, the public folder will be generated.
git init
git add .
git commit &#34;First commit&#34;
git remote add origin https://github.com/your-user-name/your-user-name.github.io.git
## connect the local site with your github repository
git push -u origin main ## -u or -f choose one 
git push -f origin main ## will replace the original version
&lt;/pre&gt;
</description>
        </item>
